import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['u'], data['v'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title("What is the overall distribution of the 2D points?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['u'], data['v'], label='Data points')
    
    X = sm.add_constant(data['u'])
    model = sm.OLS(data['v'], X).fit()
    predictions = model.predict(X)
    plt.plot(data['u'], predictions, color='red', label='Regression line')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xlabel('u')
    plt.ylabel('v')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between the u and v coordinates?')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.kdeplot(data=data, x='u', y='v', cmap='viridis', shade=True)
    plt.title("Are there any patterns or clusters in the distribution of the 2D points?", wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
